How to install Python, OpenCV and ffmpeg to convert stereo mjpeg Arducam recording to 3 mp4 files-stereo as well as left and right with frame number - and rotated:
Made by Ólavur av Fløtum Mittún (rpn797@alumni.ku.dk)

STEP 1: download Python from http://www.Python.org

STEP 2: Install Python - customize installation and "install for all users" and select "Add Python to Environment variables".
Info concerning how to install Python: https://phoenixnap.com/kb/how-to-install-python-3-windows 
Test that Python is installed - cmd - python --version

STEP 3: Install OpenCV for Python:
cmd
Pip install opencv-python
Remember to add path

STEP 4: Install ffmpeg for python: https://www.gyan.dev/ffmpeg/builds/ Download - Ffmpeg-git-full.7z
Remember to add the path - and a copy of the path including\bin:
Test if ffmepeg is installeD from cmd type ffmpeg

STEP 5: Copy directory 3D-Cam to C, D or .. drive
